mobs.name: Lesser Phantom
mobs.description: A spirit left behind in this world, now employed by larger monsters with the promise of peace.

mobs.name: Greater Phantom
mobs.description: Technically more demon than spirit, these creatures come from the depths of the underworld, given freedom from the flame in exchange for servitude to their masters.

mobs.name: Nightmare
mobs.description: Flaming beasts of the underworld, despite not being inherently malignent, these creatures are known to attack anything with the spark of life they have since lost.

mobs.name: Umbral Demon, Terror of the abyss.
mobs.description: A demon of incredible power, said to command magic and underlings alike.

mobs.name: Spirit Skull
mobs.description: A human skull possesed by a summoned, evil spirit!

mobs.name: Skeleton Lancer
mobs.description: A skeletal warrior, given life again by an evil spirit, doomed to wander the earth attacking the living.

mobs.name: Fallen Hero, Castle lord
mobs.description: An old warrior of this world, taken by the darkness forming in across the land.

mobs.name: skeleton Archer
mobs.description: A skeletal warrior given life again by an evil spirit, doomed to wander the earth attacking the living.

mobs.name: Skeleton Tank
mobs.description: A skeletal warrior of a sturdier variety

mobs.name: Nightmare Slime
mobs.description: A pool of concentrated spirits, the ugly result of souls seeping through the cracks in this world.

mobs.name: Grand Berserker
mobs.description: A corrupted hero, unlike the Fallen Hero who now sulks and rests unless disturbed, the Grand Berserker was consumed by aggression and rage.

mobs.name: Holy Knight
mobs.description: A loyal crusader in the ranks of the church.

mobs.name: Grand Holy Knight
mobs.description: A more powerful member of the holy army's ranks.

mobs.name: Seiyusael; Angel of Duality
mobs.description: An angel summoned by the most powerful magic the church has to offer, used to smite enemies deemed dangerous.

mobs.name: Sewer Ghouls
mobs.description: A monster hiding beneath the village, ready to strike and tear with its poisonous skin and razor sharp teeth.

mobs.name: King of the Underground
mobs.description: A monster lurking underneath the village since before its foundation, self appointed king of the underground. His unusual glow seems to be tied to...

mobs.name: Skeletal Dragon
mobs.description: A massive undead beast, seemingly guarding the exit to the underground areas, despite sometimes being observed above ground.

mobs.name: Black Arcanist
mobs.description: A peculiar monster, put togeather from many souls amd magics.

mobs.name: Chaos Soul Magus
mobs.description: The master of the archanist, this spell caster is capable of high tier magic attacks of all natures.

mobs.name: Death Crusader
mobs.description: The polar opposite to the crusaders of the holy church, and much more dangerous than the humans who make that up.

mobs.name: Knightmare Duke
mobs.description: A literal prince of the night, this creature rules over a good bit of the unholy spire.

mobs.name: Fallen Angel
mobs.description: A cousin to the angel of duality, except instead of balance representing complete corruption.

mobs.name: Spire ruler, Infiest
mobs.description: The hellish ruler of the unholy spire, this monster posseses a level of speed and attack second only to the dragons of old.

mobs.name: Flame Beast
mobs.description: A firey beast from beneath the surface of the world, where magma and fire reign supreme.

mobs.name: Valley Knight
mobs.description: An ancient hero said to have disapeared into the mountains after narrowly slaying a great dragon and burrying its body underground, now his body roams tainted by the darkness covering the world.

mobs.name: Nightmare Golem
mobs.description: The result of the Holy Churches experiments into summoning 'Angels', a creature of pure madness.

mobs.name: Deepsea Protector
mobs.description: Monsters living deap under the ocean floor, helping to guard ancient secrets.

mobs.name: Sunken Guardian
mobs.description: An ancient creature, guarding sunken secrets from those who cannot prove themselves to it.

mobs.name: Arch-Bishop; Holy incarnate
mobs.description: One of the heads of the holy church, and a force to be rekoned with.

mobs.name: Flare Wyvern
mobs.description: Unusual creatures spotted out in the great dessert, always running before observation.

mobs.name: Imp
mobs.description: A flame given life, an ember sparked to conciousness by ancient forces.

mobs.name: Keeper of the Flame
mobs.description: An ancient race tucked away within deep beneath the earth.

mobs.name: Protector of the Flame
mobs.description: A charred corpse given life anew by the eternal flame.

mobs.name: Blaze Incarnate: Sol
mobs.description: A living embodiment of the Eternal Flame.

mobs.name: Scorched Guardian
mobs.description: An ancient guardian sealed away with the pendant of the eternal flame.

mobs.name: Cultist of Undeath
mobs.description: The advanced guard of the Cult of Undeath, worshippers of all things undead.

mobs.name: Burried Guardian Corrupted: Undeath
mobs.description: What remains of the once proud and lush earth guardian, now twisted and undead.

mobs.name: Roaming Reaver
mobs.description: Creatures lurking in the shadows, they latch onto the living and suck them dry of energy.

mobs.name: Priest of Undeath
mobs.description: A high priest of the cult of Undeath, specializing in unholy magics that summon and empower the dead.

mobs.name: Experiment Unleashed: Gargoyl
mobs.description: A chimera formed from unwilling souls, proverbialy stitched togeather by the undead cult.

mobs.name: Dark Rebirth
mobs.description: Another one of the twisted experiments of the cult, this creature was summoned by careful spirit engineering.

mobs.name: Unshackled Abomination: Angel's Death
mobs.description: The result of an angel ballooning with darkness until losing itself, this is a very dangerous and powerful creature.

mobs.name: Gate of the Underneath
mobs.description: A Gate allowing for passage to the underworld.

mobs.name: Eternity Incarnate: Mobius
mobs.description: An ancient sculpture left in the shape of a Mobius Strip, now possessed by remnants of eternity.

mobs.name: Feathered Wind Serpent
mobs.description: Flying, usually passive creatures that soar above the sky, resting somewhere uknown.

mobs.name: Gaseous Reaver
mobs.description: A sky dwelling creature that emits a flamable gas from its back.

mobs.name: Winder Rider
mobs.description: An old protector of the ancient city, now weary and aimless with age.

mobs.name: Soaring Guardian
mobs.description: The weary guardian of the Pendant of Winds.

mobs.name: Soaring Guardian Enraged
mobs.description: The cornered anger of the soaring guardian, desperate for victory.

mobs.name: Soaring Guardian: Undeath
mobs.description: The mangled shadow of the guardian of the wind, turned undead by unholy magic.

mobs.name: Holy Inquisitor
mobs.description: A swift assassin for the church, ready to strike at any time.

mobs.name: Grand Crusader
mobs.description: A military authority of the church, ready to strike down any enemies that stand in the way of doctrine.

mobs.name: Overseer of Heroes
mobs.description: An attendant charged with protecting the ancient heroes before their time of awakening.

mobs.name: Hero of Holy Light: Imperitus
mobs.description: A great warrior for the church, who rose above the ranks to become a hero!

mobs.name: Hero of Holy Light: Asphur
mobs.description: One of the 3 Heroes of the Holy Light, asphur rests for the day the church calls on him again.

mobs.name: Ashpur: Enraged
mobs.description: The true form of the mighty hero of light!

mobs.name: Hero of Holy Light: Aethel
mobs.description: The greatest of the Heroes of Holy Light, Aethel's incredible power is sealed until the right time.

mobs.name: Aethel: Enraged
mobs.description: The true form of the greatest hero of light!

mobs.name: Bloodcrystal Titan
mobs.description: A monster born from blood crystals near the dark vortex hiding deep within the earth.

mobs.name: Diamond Titan
mobs.description: A monster created by the negative energy of the void seeping into diamond crystals.

mobs.name: Mantle Incarnate
mobs.description: A monster born from the very magma underneath the earth.

mobs.name: Expression of Void
mobs.description: A simple manifestation of the void's agression, these creatures lurk in the boundary to darkness.

mobs.name: Keeper of death
mobs.description: A guardian of the ultimate undead weapon, the reaper himself.

mobs.name: Keeper of death Enraged
mobs.description: The true power of death unleashed!

mobs.name: Reaper of Soul
mobs.description: The deathbringer, The angel of death, The end of all things.

mobs.name: Reaper: Uncloaked
mobs.description: The bursting warrior form of the reaper.

mobs.name: Reaper Uncloaked, Enraged
mobs.description: A channeling of death itself in all its glory.

mobs.name: Silhouette of Abyss
mobs.description: A lingering outline of the void, unknown in its purpose or nature.

mobs.name: Ruin of Abyss
mobs.description: A rutheless creature born from the chaotic heart of the void.

mobs.name: Voice of Abyss
mobs.description: A silent but deadly assassin of the void, this creature stalks its prey before a quick execution.

mobs.name: Guard of Abyss
mobs.description: A more unmoving guard than the usual monster from the void, the guard displays its true wrath when tempered..

mobs.name: Eldritch of Abyss
mobs.description: A visually small, but terrifying creature, presumed to be a kind of follower to the horrors lying in wait beyond the edge of the abyss.

mobs.name: Wrath of Abyss
mobs.description: An incarnation of the abyss's wrath, fierce and without reason.

mobs.name: GuilForm Bastion
mobs.description: An incarnate test of your guild's might focused on well rounded stats

mobs.name: GuildForm Paragon
mobs.description: An incarnate test of your guild's might focused on magic attack.

mobs.name: GuildForm Guardian
mobs.description: An incarnate test of your guild's might focused on defenses.

mobs.name: GuildForm Piercer
mobs.description: An incarnate test of your guild's might focused on attack.

mobs.name: Unexpected Flame: Competition.
mobs.description: A rare monster spawned by the spirit of cooperation, competition, and ambition.

mobs.name: GuildForm Forge
mobs.description: The firey pit from where guild items are forged.

mobs.name: GuildForm IronWall
mobs.description: An incarnate test of your guild focused on defenses.

mobs.name: GuildForm Winder
mobs.description: An incrnate test of your guild focused on attack.

mobs.name: Padoru
mobs.description: Padoru Padoru!

mobs.name: Snow_Owl
mobs.description: A norhtern owl.

mobs.name: Northern Stag
mobs.description: A creature from the forrests of snow to the north of animelee's world.

mobs.name: Frost-Wyvern
mobs.description: A spirit from the forrests of ice, deadly and aggressive to those who would do it harm.

mobs.name: Holy Spartan
mobs.description: One of the many spearheads of the church.

mobs.name: Holy Lance
mobs.description: A more literal spearhead of the chirch, it is said that the sound of their clanging armor spells death for a village.

mobs.name: Right Hand: Descence
mobs.description: The right hand of the church, and weilder of a strong holy power.

mobs.name: Arch-Bishop: Holy incarnate
mobs.description: Unknown

mobs.name: Spectre of ancients: Ahl'Am Eos
mobs.description: ɬųཞŋ ცąƈƙ ŋơῳ

mobs.name: HealthFlyer
mobs.description: A small beatle found around poison veins beneath the earth.

mobs.name: Maiden of the Flame
mobs.description: A religious maiden left lost in the desert, eventually its flame would burn her very soul, and light it ablaze.

mobs.name: Flame Crystalid
mobs.description: A pillar of sentient flame, some say a faint screaming can be heard behind the crackling of fire.

mobs.name: Ancient Winds: Soeuil
mobs.description: A mythical being known as the wind bringer, Soeuil has long vanished to the heights of the sky, away from the increasingly corrupt land.

mobs.name: Soul Koi
mobs.description: Creatures found riding the winds, said to be the souls of humans making their way towards the heavens.

mobs.name: Spirit of War-Drum
mobs.description: The spirits of envoy parties long gone, these dutiful drummers encourage to the beat of the music.

mobs.name: Zhuge Liang
mobs.description: A servant from fate/grand order, zhuge found himself stuck in the world of animelee, however the player who spawned him was long dead.

mobs.name: Phantom Scripture
mobs.description: A spirit rarely seen, said to hold decrees from the very gods themselves.

mobs.name: Bull of Utu
mobs.description: A golden bull said to bring fortune to those who encounter it.

mobs.name: Ice Candy Bear
mobs.description: A white bear appearing to be ice, but actually being made of a cold gummy candy.

mobs.name: Candy Devourer
mobs.description: A beast displaying a ravenous hunger for all things candy.

mobs.name: Candy Glutton
mobs.description: Known to all of candy kind as a one-stop disaster, this beast will stop at nothing to consume all it can.

mobs.name: Echo of Corruption: Saber Alter
mobs.description: An echo from other worlds, appearing in the world between worlds.

mobs.name: Echo of Madness: Ryunosuke
mobs.description: A powerful man who weilds the ability Rashōmon with deadly intent.

mobs.name: Mirror of Worlds
mobs.description: A phantom that roams the spaceless realm, said to be able to reflect back infinite entities and places from infinite realities.

mobs.name: Realm Keeper
mobs.description: Abandoned Golems left behind in the twilight, who now serve as gatekeepers to its secrets.

mobs.name: Realm Hunter
mobs.description: A reflection that stayed, and now serves as the faithfull hunter of intruders for the twilight.

mobs.name: True Echo: Alter
mobs.description: The festering remnant of Alter Saber, manifesting in the Depths of twilight.

mobs.name: Forgotten Banshee
mobs.description: A spirit unteathered from the world, left to wander the abandoned twilights for eternity.

mobs.name: Phantom Echo: Cherubimon
mobs.description: A digimon infected with virulent code, corrupting everything it comes in contact with.

mobs.name: Anomylous Echo: Wallpurgis Naught
mobs.description: E-AM908 N327-NCAR98-8A743958FENDH

mobs.name: Mechanized Order
mobs.description: Slave of system, Master of User.

mobs.name: Reduction Omega
mobs.description: Mechanized Warrior of average class.

mobs.name: System Guard
mobs.description: Overseer and guardrian of the system.

mobs.name: Anomylous Echo: Wallpurgis Naught
mobs.description: E-AM908 N327-NCAR98-8A743958FENDH

mobs.name: Ulquiorra Cifer
mobs.description: One of the stronger Arrancar, Ulquiorra longs to understand the solitude within his own soul.

mobs.name: Grimmjow Jeagerjaques
mobs.description: A hollow unmatched in savagery, Grimmjow clawed his way to the top from the very bottom.

mobs.name: Ichigo Kurosaki
mobs.description: A substitute soul reaper with moxy!

mobs.name: Rukia Kuchiki
mobs.description: Daughter of the prestigious kuchiki line, rukia is an honors soul reaper if there ever was one.

mobs.name: Tosen Kaname
mobs.description: A soul reaper captain turned traitor to follow Aizen, he seeks power above all else.

mobs.name: Gin Ichimaru
mobs.description: Another one of the Captains to betray the soul society to follow aizen, his villainous demeanor may yet betray noble intent.

mobs.name: Hollowfying Ichigo
mobs.description: Channeling the power of a hollow, ichigo gains power.. and madness.

mobs.name: Hollow Ichigo
mobs.description: The true identity of the strongest of the Espada.

mobs.name: Healing light: Orihime
mobs.description: Orihime is able to use the power of spirit companions to heal and support those she cares about.

mobs.name: Baraggan Louisenbairn
mobs.description: The self proclaimed king of Hueco Mundo, Baraggan considers himself an unstoppable force of death.

mobs.name: Number 0: Yammy LLargo
mobs.description: The true strongest of the espada.

mobs.name: El Murcielago: Ulquiorra
mobs.description: The true form of Ulquiorra unleashed, he gains great speed and power.

mobs.name: Searing Land: Groudon
mobs.description: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

mobs.name: Drowning Sea: Kyogre
mobs.description: Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.

mobs.name: Sceptile
mobs.description: The leaves on its forelegs are as sharp as swords. It agilely leaps about the branches of trees to strike.

mobs.name: Blaziken
mobs.description: BLAZIKEN has incredibly strong legs - it can easily clear a 30-story building in one leap. This POKéMON’s blazing punches leave its foes scorched and blackened.

mobs.name: Swampert
mobs.description: SWAMPERT predicts storms by sensing subtle differences in the sounds of waves and tidal winds with its fins. If a storm is approaching, it piles up boulders to protect itself.

mobs.name: Great Sky Dragon: Rayquaza
mobs.description: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

mobs.name: Mega Rayquaza
mobs.description: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

mobs.name: Demon moon company: Yuichiro
mobs.description: Youngest member of the anti-vampire special unit of the military.

mobs.name: Demon moon company: Shinoa
mobs.description: A descendant of the ruling family, Shinoa instead puts her life at risk with the rest of the demon moon company.

mobs.name: Ferid Bathory
mobs.description: The 7th progenitor and overseer of human camps in the vampire cities of japan.

mobs.name: Krul Tepes
mobs.description: The ruler of vampires in japan, krul is a direct descendant of the original vampire, making her extremely powerful.

mobs.name: Mikaela Hyakuya
mobs.description: An orphan of the hyakuya sect that was unable to escape the vampire's clutches, where he became one himself

mobs.name: Spire's Vanguard: Palorael
mobs.description: Watcher over the levels of the unholy spire, said to have been an angel once before.

mobs.name: Dark Sol
mobs.description: A withered echo of a warrior once proudly devoted to the light. Rumor has it all those devoted to the heavens end up this way eventually.

mobs.name: True Arch-Duke
mobs.description: In contrast to the fallen Sol, the Arch-Duke thrives within the power of the spire.

mobs.name: Edge of Depth
mobs.description: A monstrous being, amalgamated from the hearts of that which human minds fail to comprehend.

mobs.name: Heavens Tremor
mobs.description: An ancient being of the sky, legends have it this creature danced through the skies, its steps causing the very skies above to tremble.
